## CI/CD WORKFLOWS
```
.github/workflows/
├── ci.yml                ← Multi-compiler build + test + lcov coverage
├── codeql.yml            ← Security analysis (C++ security-extended)
├── dependency-review.yml ← PR dependency vulnerability check
└── fuzz.yml              ← libFuzzer with ASan + UBSan (60s PR / 300s nightly)
```

## QUICK REFERENCE — BEFORE YOU START ANY TAR
1. Ask the user for the TAR number and description
2. Read the CDRL Register: `docs/cdrl/CDRL-Register.md`
3. Read the SRS and find applicable requirements: `docs/requirements/SRS-SynthFlight.md`
4. Look up the WBS element for the module in the SRS
5. Confirm the DAL level from PROJECT IDENTITY above
6. Read the code standard: `docs/standards/SCS-SynthFlight.md`
7. Read the verification plan: `docs/plans/SVP-SynthFlight.md`
8. Verify all plans are baselined (check status in CDRL Register)
9. Present your findings and ask "Is this correct?" before proceeding
10. Do the work (follow the 5-phase workflow from the global .goosehints)
11. Update the CDRL Register with any new or modified deliverables
12. Present what will be committed and ask for approval before committing